Shigellosis, homeless shelter - USA (Wisconsin) 980801091917
Date: Sat, 01 Aug 1998 18:33:06 +0000
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on shigellosis in the United States were
abstracted from the GIDEON software program:

Years Cases reported
1944-1983 684,503
1990 27,077
1991 23,548
1992 23,931
1993 32,198
1994 29,769
1995 32,080 (the 6th leading reported infectious disease that year)
1996 25,978
790 food-related outbreaks were registered during 1973 to 1987, and 25
water-related outbreaks during 1972 to 1990. Two waterborne outbreaks (260
cases) were reported during 1993 to 1994.
Fatal infections decreased from 894 during [the period from 1961 to 1970,
to 104
during 1982 to 1991. Two hundred and twenty-seven children below age 5 died
of shigellosis during 1968 to 1991. Eight fatal infections (all ages) were
reported in 1992; 5 in 1993; 13 in 1994; 8 in 1995.
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
